50|$|The {{output stages}} of both devices are similar, but the input stages are quite different. There is no {{baseband}} audio or video input to the translator. The translator receives an over-the air RF input signal {{by means of}} an antenna, just like a <b>home</b> <b>receiver.</b> Since received signal is already modulated {{there is no need for}} a modulator. Instead an input mixer or down-converter shifts the radio-frequency (RF) signal down to an intermediate-frequency (IF) signal. A second mixer (known as output mixer or up-converter) shifts the IF signal back up to the FM or TV band output signal frequency.|$|E
