50|$|The Digital Media Port (DMP or DMPort) is an {{interface}} for analog {{audio and}} video signal and digital control that Sony has started to propose on its A/V products in 2007. As of January 2009, Sony {{seems to be the}} only manufacturer proposing this interface. They offer different accessories to connect DMP ready equipment like their Bravia TV or <b>Home</b> Theater <b>receivers</b> to Walkman, iPod, PC or any Bluetooth devices.|$|R
